13 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Marijuana tax revenue accountability council -- definition. (1) The re
14 is a marijuana tax revenue accountability council attached to the department of public health and human
15 services for administrative purposes only as prescribed in 2-15-121.
16 (2) The council is composed of the following members:
17 (a) the director of the department of public health and human services or a designee;
18 (b) a representative of the department of justice appointed by the attorney general;
19 (c) a representative of the department of revenue appointed by the director of the department of
20 revenue ;
21 (d) one member who also serves on the board of behavioral health provided for in 2-15-1744
22 appointed by the presiding officer of the board of behavioral health;
23 (e) one member who represents the behavioral health alliance of Montana and who is dually
24 licensed as an addiction counselor and as a licensed practitioner or is a master's social work licensee
25 appointed by the governor;
26 (f) one member who represents the behavioral health alliance of Montana and who is a licensed
27 psychiatrist appointed by the governor;
28 (g) one member who is a certified prevention specialist appointed by the governor; and
